  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Mongolia: Competition: Legal Reform and Institutional Capacity Building</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1) To assist with drafting amendments to the Advertisement law. 2) To provide high quality professionally-relevant training to the Authority for Fair Competition and Consumer Protections (AFCCP) investigators and staff to strengthen their ability to enforce the legislation under the purview of the AFCCP. 3) To advise on mechanisms to establish effective coordination and collaboration between the AFCCP and sector regulators such as telecommunications, electricity and air transportation entities. 4) To foster a platform for dialogue and understanding between the AFCCP and the Judiciary in order to properly handle the competition-related cases in courts.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Direct beneficiaries: The AFCCP, the Judiciary and sector regulators, such as the Electricity Coordination Board and the
Communications Coordination Board. Indirect beneficiaries: Citizens of Mongolia.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aims to foster free market competition by legislative drafting support, advocacy and tailored assistance to the Government Agency for Fair Competition and Consumer Protection (AFCCP).</narrative>
  </description>
